  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You produce a fire that entrances the fates, distracting them from aiding your foes. Whenever you deal fire damage to a creature or object, they take an extra [[/damage 1d6 fire]] damage. If you deal fire damage to a mundane object, you can use a free triggered action to target it with your @UUID[Compendium.draw-steel.abilities.Item.vldbnWQnyytdagrH]{Return to Formlessness} ability instead.</p><p>Additionally, any enemy who starts their turn adjacent to you has [[/apply uqiVDBgnxj1UMTDp]] equal to [[lookup @R]]{your Reason score} until the start of their next turn. This increases to [[lookup 2*@R evaluate=true]]{twice your Reason score} if the enemy is made of or is wearing mostly metal [[/apply SEJIkEUllUvEYgbk]].</p>",
      "director": ""
    },
